00:01:11.810 --> 00:01:15.520
Congress has the power to make rules concerning
the Armed Forces, so let's say this is a bill

00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:19.240
about naming helicopters. Anywho, this bill
would be referred to the Senate Armed Services

00:01:19.240 --> 00:01:23.080
Committee, which would then write up the bill
in formal, legal language, or markup, and vote on it.

00:01:23.080 --> 00:01:27.139
If the markup wins a majority in the committee,
it moves to the floor of the full Senate for consideration.

00:01:27.139 --> 00:01:30.429
The Senate decides the rules for debate - how
long the debate will go on and whether or

00:01:30.429 --> 00:01:33.929
not there will be amendments. An open rule
allows for amendments and a closed rule does

00:01:33.929 --> 00:01:37.579
not. Open rules make it much less likely for
bills to pass because proponents of the bill

00:01:37.579 --> 00:01:40.969
can add clauses that will make it hard for
the bill's proponents to vote for.

00:01:40.969 --> 00:01:44.560
If opponents of our helicopter name bill were
